<h2 id="typefaces">Typefaces</h2>
<p>Protocol comes with three fonts: Metropolis, Zilla Slab, and Inter.</p>
<p>Firefox branded websites use Metropolis for titles and Inter for body text. Don't use Metropolis for body text.</p>
<p>Mozilla branded websites use Zilla Slab for titles and Inter for body text. Don't use Zilla Slab for body text.</p>

<h3 id="typeface-inter">Inter</h3>
<p>Inter is an open source, sans-serif font was designed by <a href="https://rsms.me/">Rasmus Andersson</a>. This is our standard type face for body copy in both Firefox and Mozilla brands. If you need to declare it specifically (such as to override some other inherited font) you can use the mixin <code class="language-scss">@include font-base;</code>.</p>

