<h3 id="typeface-metropolis">Metropolis</h3>

<p>Metropolis is a free, open source font used for headlines on marketing and product web experiences. It's a geometric sans-serif font by Chris Simpson, very similar in style and character to Firefox Sharp Sans, the proprietary font used to create logo lockups for Firefox products (<strong>do not use Firefox Sharp Sans as a webfont</strong>).
<p>Use Metropolis for large text like headings. As a general rule, type set in Metroplis should stand out. Avoid stacking two sizes of Metropolis one on top of the other. Pair headings in Metropolis with subheadings in Inter.</p>
<p>You can declare Metropolis explicitly with the mixin <code class="language-scss">@include font-firefox;</code>.</p>
<p>Don't italicize Metropolis. Protocol only includes normal and bold versions of this font.</p>

